                <fr:title text="Addition of complex numbers">Addition of complex numbers</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/lankham-2016-linear/" title="Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics" uri="http://localhost:8000/lankham-2016-linear/" display-uri="lankham-2016-linear" type="local">Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics</fr:link> §2.2.1</fr:meta>
                <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/axler-1996-linear/" title="Linear Algebra Done Right" uri="http://localhost:8000/axler-1996-linear/" display-uri="axler-1996-linear" type="local">Linear Algebra Done Right</fr:link> 1.1</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>We define the <html:dfn>Addition</html:dfn> of complex numbers as the binary operator <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[+]]></fr:tex> by
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[(a+\mathrm {i} b)+(c+\mathrm {i} d)=(a+c)+\mathrm {i}(b+d)]]></fr:tex></html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
