                <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/lankham-2016-linear/" title="Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics" uri="http://localhost:8000/lankham-2016-linear/" display-uri="lankham-2016-linear" type="local">Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics</fr:link> Definition 2.2.8</fr:meta>
                <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/axler-1996-linear/" title="Linear Algebra Done Right" uri="http://localhost:8000/axler-1996-linear/" display-uri="axler-1996-linear" type="local">Linear Algebra Done Right</fr:link> Definition 4.2</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z=x+\mathrm {i} y\in \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> be a complex number with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y\in \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>. Then we define the <html:dfn>Complex Conjugate</html:dfn> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z]]></fr:tex> to be the complex number <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\overline {z}=x-\mathrm {i} y]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
