                <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/axler-1996-linear/" title="Linear Algebra Done Right" uri="http://localhost:8000/axler-1996-linear/" display-uri="axler-1996-linear" type="local">Linear Algebra Done Right</fr:link> Theorem 4.4</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z_{1},z_{2}\in \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> be complex numbers. Then the following all hold:</html:p>
                <html:ol><html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|z_{1}z_{2}|=|z_{1}|\cdot |z_{2}|]]></fr:tex></html:li>
<html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|z_{1}/z_{2}|=|z_{1}|/|z_{2}|]]></fr:tex></html:li>
<html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|\overline {z_{1}}|=|z_{1}|]]></fr:tex></html:li>
<html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|\Re (z_{1})|\leq |z_{1}|]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|\Im (z_{1})|\leq |z_{1}|]]></fr:tex></html:li>
<html:li>Triangle inequality: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|z_{1}+z_{2}|\leq |z_{1}|+|z_{2}|]]></fr:tex></html:li>
<html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|z_{1}-z_{2}|\geq ||z_{1}|-|z_{2}||]]></fr:tex></html:li>
<html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z_{1}\overline {z_{1}}=|z_{1}|^{2}]]></fr:tex> which implies when <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z_{1}\neq 0]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[z_{1}^{-1}=\frac {\overline {z_{1}}}{|z_{1}|^{2}}]]></fr:tex></html:li></html:ol>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
