                <fr:route>/complex-000A/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Polar form for complex numbers">Polar form for complex numbers</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/lankham-2016-linear/" title="Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics" uri="http://localhost:8000/lankham-2016-linear/" display-uri="lankham-2016-linear" type="local">Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics</fr:link> 2.3.1</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z=x+\mathrm {i} y]]></fr:tex> be a complex number where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y\in \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>. Then we define the <html:dfn>Argument</html:dfn> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z]]></fr:tex> to be the number <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\theta =\mathop {\textrm {Arg}}\nolimits (z)]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0\leq \theta <2\pi ]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x=|z|\cos (\theta )]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y=|z|\sin (\theta )]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
                <html:p>We can also write this in exponential form as <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z=|z|\mathop {\textrm {exp}}\nolimits (\mathrm {i}\theta )]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
