                <fr:display-uri>complex-000C</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/complex-000C/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="de Moivre's formula">de Moivre's formula</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>theorem</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/lankham-2016-linear/" title="Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics" uri="http://localhost:8000/lankham-2016-linear/" display-uri="lankham-2016-linear" type="local">Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics</fr:link> Theorem 2.3.3</fr:meta>
                <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/axler-1996-linear/" title="Linear Algebra Done Right" uri="http://localhost:8000/axler-1996-linear/" display-uri="axler-1996-linear" type="local">Linear Algebra Done Right</fr:link> Theorem 4.4</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z=r(\cos (\theta )+\mathrm {i}\sin (\theta ))]]></fr:tex> be a complex number in polar form. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n\in \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> be a positive integer. Then:</html:p>
                <html:ol><html:li>The exponentiation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z^{n}=r^{n}(\cos (n\theta )+\mathrm {i}\sin (n\theta ))]]></fr:tex>;</html:li>
<html:li>The <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n^{\text {th}}]]></fr:tex> roots of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z]]></fr:tex> are given by the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> complex numbers <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z_{k}=r^{1/n}[\cos ((\theta +2\pi  k)/n)+\mathrm {i}\sin ((\theta +2\pi  k)/n)]]]></fr:tex>.</html:li></html:ol>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
