                <fr:display-uri>complex-000D</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/complex-000D/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Root of unity">Root of unity</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/lankham-2016-linear/" title="Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics" uri="http://localhost:8000/lankham-2016-linear/" display-uri="lankham-2016-linear" type="local">Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics</fr:link> Section 2.3</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n\in \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex>. We define the <html:dfn><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n^{\text {th}}]]></fr:tex> Root of Unity</html:dfn> to be <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1^{1/n}=\cos (2\pi  k/n)+\mathrm {i}\sin (2\pi  k/n)]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k=1,…,n]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
