                <fr:title text="Complex exponential">Complex exponential</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/lankham-2016-linear/" title="Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics" uri="http://localhost:8000/lankham-2016-linear/" display-uri="lankham-2016-linear" type="local">Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics</fr:link> Section 2.3.4</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z=x+\mathrm {i} y]]></fr:tex> be a complex number with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y\in \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>. Then we define the <html:dfn>Complex Exponential</html:dfn> to be a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathop {\textrm {exp}}\nolimits \colon \mathbb {C}\to \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> defined by
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\mathop {\textrm {exp}}\nolimits (z)=\mathrm {e}^{x}\mathrm {e}^{\mathrm {i} y}=\mathrm {e}^{x}(\cos (y)+\mathrm {i}\sin (y))]]></fr:tex></html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
