                <fr:title text="Complex sine and cosine">Complex sine and cosine</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/lankham-2016-linear/" title="Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics" uri="http://localhost:8000/lankham-2016-linear/" display-uri="lankham-2016-linear" type="local">Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics</fr:link> Section 2.3.4</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z=x+\mathrm {i} y]]></fr:tex> be a complex number with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y\in \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>. Then we define the <html:dfn>Complex Sine</html:dfn> function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sin \colon \mathbb {C}\to \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> by
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\sin (z) = \frac {\mathrm {e}^{\mathrm {i} z}-\mathrm {e}^{-\mathrm {i} z}}{2\mathrm {i}}]]></fr:tex>
Similarly we define the <html:dfn>Complex Cosine</html:dfn> function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\cos \colon \mathbb {C}\to \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> by
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\cos (z) = \frac {\mathrm {e}^{\mathrm {i} z}+\mathrm {e}^{-\mathrm {i} z}}{2\mathrm {i}}]]></fr:tex></html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
