                <fr:route>/complex-000G/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Properties of complex exponential and trigonometric functions">Properties of complex exponential and trigonometric functions</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>theorem</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/lankham-2016-linear/" title="Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics" uri="http://localhost:8000/lankham-2016-linear/" display-uri="lankham-2016-linear" type="local">Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics</fr:link> Theorem 2.3.5</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z_{1},z_{2}\in \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>. Then the following all hold:</html:p>
                <html:ol><html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {e}^{z_{1}+z_{2}}=\mathrm {e}^{z_{1}}\mathrm {e}^{z_{2}}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {e}^{z}\neq 0]]></fr:tex> for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z\in \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex></html:li>
<html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sin ^{2}(z_{1})+\cos ^{2}(z_{1})=1]]></fr:tex></html:li>
<html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sin (z_{1}+z_{2})=\sin (z_{1})\cos (z_{2})+\cos (z_{1})\sin (z_{2})]]></fr:tex></html:li>
<html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\cos (z_{1}+z_{2})=\cos (z_{1})\cos (z_{2})-\sin (z_{1})\sin (z_{2})]]></fr:tex></html:li></html:ol>
              </fr:mainmatter>
